1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:01,950
Welcome to box breathing.

2
00:00:01,950 --> 00:00:07,612
This is a simple breathing practice that
can help your system slow down and find a

3
00:00:07,612 --> 00:00:08,730
steadier rhythm.

4
00:00:08,730 --> 00:00:16,221
We will breathe in for four counts, hold
for four counts, breathe out for four

5
00:00:16,221 --> 00:00:20,015
counts, and hold again for four counts.

6
00:00:26,015 --> 00:00:26,015
<break time="3s" />

7
00:00:26,015 --> 00:00:32,749
If holding your breath does not feel
good, you can simply breathe gently and

8
00:00:32,749 --> 00:00:34,096
skip the holds.

9
00:00:40,096 --> 00:00:40,096
<break time="3s" />

10
00:00:40,096 --> 00:00:43,486
Let this practice be flexible.

11
00:00:43,486 --> 00:00:49,245
Begin by settling into a comfortable
position.

12
00:00:49,245 --> 00:00:52,914
Let your shoulders soften if they can.

13
00:00:52,914 --> 00:00:55,515
Let your jaw loosen.

14
00:00:55,515 --> 00:00:58,162
Let your hands rest.

15
00:00:58,162 --> 00:01:01,088
Take one natural breath in.

16
00:01:01,088 --> 00:01:02,806
And let it out.

17
00:01:02,806 --> 00:01:04,524
Now we’ll begin.

18
00:01:04,524 --> 00:01:06,267
Breathe in .

19
00:01:06,267 --> 00:01:07,428
One.

20
00:01:07,428 --> 00:01:08,496
Two.

21
00:01:08,496 --> 00:01:09,796
Three.

22
00:01:09,796 --> 00:01:12,397
Four.

23
00:01:12,397 --> 00:01:15,276
Hold.

24
00:01:15,276 --> 00:01:18,852
One.

25
00:01:18,852 --> 00:01:20,106
Two.

26
00:01:20,106 --> 00:01:21,406
Three.

27
00:01:21,406 --> 00:01:22,660
Four.

28
00:01:22,660 --> 00:01:24,053
Breathe out.

29
00:01:24,053 --> 00:01:24,471
One.

30
00:01:24,471 --> 00:01:25,818
Two.

31
00:01:25,818 --> 00:01:27,676
Three.

32
00:01:27,676 --> 00:01:29,209
Four.

33
00:01:29,209 --> 00:01:32,413
Hold.

34
00:01:32,413 --> 00:01:33,574
One.

35
00:01:33,574 --> 00:01:34,642
Two.

36
00:01:34,642 --> 00:01:35,942
Three.

37
00:01:35,942 --> 00:01:37,057
Four.

38
00:01:37,057 --> 00:01:38,497
Good.

39
00:01:38,497 --> 00:01:39,333
Again.

40
00:01:39,333 --> 00:01:42,444
Breathe in.

41
00:01:42,444 --> 00:01:42,908
One.

42
00:01:42,908 --> 00:01:44,255
Two.

43
00:01:44,255 --> 00:01:45,555
Three.

44
00:01:45,555 --> 00:01:48,388
Four.

45
00:01:48,388 --> 00:01:51,267
Hold.

46
00:01:51,267 --> 00:01:52,428
One.

47
00:01:52,428 --> 00:01:53,496
Two.

48
00:01:53,496 --> 00:01:54,843
Three.

49
00:01:54,843 --> 00:01:56,097
Four.

50
00:01:56,097 --> 00:01:57,490
Breathe out.

51
00:01:57,490 --> 00:01:57,908
One.

52
00:01:57,908 --> 00:01:58,697
Two.

53
00:01:58,697 --> 00:01:59,672
Three.

54
00:01:59,672 --> 00:02:01,205
Four.

55
00:02:01,205 --> 00:02:02,970
Hold.

56
00:02:02,970 --> 00:02:04,085
One.

57
00:02:04,085 --> 00:02:05,153
Two.

58
00:02:05,153 --> 00:02:06,546
Three.

59
00:02:06,546 --> 00:02:08,357
Four.

60
00:02:08,357 --> 00:02:13,930
Let your body follow the rhythm as much
as it wants to.

61
00:02:13,930 --> 00:02:15,555
Breathe in.

62
00:02:15,555 --> 00:02:18,945
One.

63
00:02:18,945 --> 00:02:20,199
Two.

64
00:02:20,199 --> 00:02:21,592
Three.

65
00:02:21,592 --> 00:02:24,425
Four.

66
00:02:24,425 --> 00:02:27,304
Hold.

67
00:02:27,304 --> 00:02:27,815
On.

68
00:02:27,815 --> 00:02:29,162
Two.

69
00:02:29,162 --> 00:02:30,416
Three.

70
00:02:30,416 --> 00:02:34,131
Four.

71
00:02:34,131 --> 00:02:35,896
Breathe out.

72
00:02:35,896 --> 00:02:36,407
One.

73
00:02:36,407 --> 00:02:37,196
Two.

74
00:02:37,196 --> 00:02:39,054
Three.

75
00:02:39,054 --> 00:02:40,587
Four.

76
00:02:40,587 --> 00:02:43,791
Hold.

77
00:02:43,791 --> 00:02:44,255
One.

78
00:02:44,255 --> 00:02:45,509
Two.

79
00:02:45,509 --> 00:02:47,042
Three.

80
00:02:47,042 --> 00:02:48,249
Four.

81
00:02:48,249 --> 00:02:51,639
If your mind wanders, that is okay.

82
00:02:51,639 --> 00:02:54,193
Just come back to the next count.

83
00:02:54,193 --> 00:02:56,143
Breathe in.

84
00:02:56,143 --> 00:02:56,607
One.

85
00:02:56,607 --> 00:02:57,814
Two.

86
00:02:57,814 --> 00:02:59,114
Three.

87
00:02:59,114 --> 00:03:01,947
Four.

88
00:03:01,947 --> 00:03:04,826
Hold.

89
00:03:04,826 --> 00:03:05,290
One.

90
00:03:05,290 --> 00:03:06,358
Two.

91
00:03:06,358 --> 00:03:07,705
Three.

92
00:03:07,705 --> 00:03:11,420
Four.

93
00:03:11,420 --> 00:03:12,813
Breathe out.

94
00:03:12,813 --> 00:03:13,324
One.

95
00:03:13,324 --> 00:03:14,113
Two.

96
00:03:14,113 --> 00:03:14,856
Three.

97
00:03:14,856 --> 00:03:16,389
Four.

98
00:03:16,389 --> 00:03:18,154
Hold.

99
00:03:27,154 --> 00:03:27,154
<break time="3s" />

100
00:03:27,154 --> 00:03:28,501
One.

101
00:03:28,501 --> 00:03:29,755
Two.

102
00:03:29,755 --> 00:03:31,288
Three.

103
00:03:31,288 --> 00:03:32,449
Four.

104
00:03:32,449 --> 00:03:35,793
Now let the counting become softer.

105
00:03:35,793 --> 00:03:38,904
Breathe in for four.

106
00:03:42,904 --> 00:03:42,904
<break time="1s" />

107
00:03:42,904 --> 00:03:44,901
Hold for four.

108
00:03:48,901 --> 00:03:48,901
<break time="1s" />

109
00:03:48,901 --> 00:03:51,316
Breathe out for four.

110
00:03:51,316 --> 00:03:53,592
Hold for four.

111
00:03:57,592 --> 00:03:57,592
<break time="1s" />

112
00:03:57,592 --> 00:03:58,846
Again.

113
00:03:58,846 --> 00:04:00,471
Breathe in.

114
00:04:04,471 --> 00:04:04,471
<break time="1s" />

115
00:04:04,471 --> 00:04:05,818
Hold.

116
00:04:09,818 --> 00:04:09,818
<break time="1s" />

117
00:04:09,818 --> 00:04:11,490
Breathe out.

118
00:04:11,490 --> 00:04:12,790
Hold.

119
00:04:16,790 --> 00:04:16,790
<break time="1s" />

120
00:04:16,790 --> 00:04:19,437
Now release the counting.

121
00:04:19,437 --> 00:04:25,614
Let your breathing return to whatever
pace feels natural.

122
00:04:34,614 --> 00:04:34,614
<break time="3s" />

123
00:04:34,614 --> 00:04:36,657
Notice your body.

124
00:04:48,657 --> 00:04:48,657
<break time="3s" /><break time="3s" />

125
00:04:48,657 --> 00:04:50,515
Notice your breath.

126
00:04:50,515 --> 00:04:55,763
Notice whether anything inside feels even
slightly more settled.

127
00:04:55,763 --> 00:05:00,407
If parts of you still feel activated,
that is okay.

128
00:05:00,407 --> 00:05:03,054
The goal is not to force calm.

129
00:05:03,054 --> 00:05:07,512
The goal is to offer your system a steady
rhythm.

130
00:05:07,512 --> 00:05:10,949
Take one final breath in.

131
00:05:10,949 --> 00:05:13,178
And let it out slowly.

132
00:05:13,178 --> 00:05:18,147
When you are ready, return your attention
to the room around you.

133
00:05:18,147 --> 00:05:24,416
Let this rhythm be something you can come
back to — not as a command to calm down,

134
00:05:24,416 --> 00:05:29,989
but as a steady square of support your
body can lean on when it is ready.

